{"name": "async-generator", "metadata": {"name": "async_generator", "version": "1.10", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Framework :: AsyncIO", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy"], "home_page": "https://github.com/python-trio/async_generator", "license": "MIT -or- Apache License 2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Async generators and context managers for Python 3.5+", "upload_time": 1533094580}, "documentation": ["```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/chat-join%20now-blue.svg\n:alt: Join chatroom\n:target: https://gitter.im/python-trio/general\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-read%20now-blue.svg\n:alt: Documentation Status\n:target: https://async-generator.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n```\n\n```{image} https://travis-ci.org/python-trio/async_generator.svg?branch=master\n:alt: Automated test status\n:target: https://travis-ci.org/python-trio/async_generator\n```\n\n```{image} https://ci.appveyor.com/api/projects/status/af4eyed8o8tc3t0r/branch/master?svg=true\n:alt: Automated test status (Windows)\n:target: https://ci.appveyor.com/project/python-trio/trio/history\n```\n\n```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/python-trio/async_generator/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n:alt: Test coverage\n:target: https://codecov.io/gh/python-trio/async_generator\n```\n\n# The async_generator library\n\nPython 3.6 added [async generators](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0525/). (What's an async\ngenerator? [Check out my 5-minute lightning talk demo from PyCon 2016](https://youtu.be/PulzIT8KYLk?t=24m30s).) Python 3.7 adds some more\ntools to make them usable, like `contextlib.asynccontextmanager`.\n\nThis library gives you all that back to Python 3.5.\n\nFor example, this code only works in Python 3.6+:\n\n```python3\nasync def load_json_lines(stream_reader):\n    async for line in stream_reader:\n        yield json.loads(line)\n```\n\nBut this code does the same thing, and works on Python 3.5+:\n\n```python3\nfrom async_generator import async_generator, yield_\n\n@async_generator\nasync def load_json_lines(stream_reader):\n    async for line in stream_reader:\n        await yield_(json.loads(line))\n```\n\nOr in Python 3.7, you can write:\n\n```python3\nfrom contextlib import asynccontextmanager\n\n@asynccontextmanager\nasync def background_server():\n    async with trio.open_nursery() as nursery:\n        value = await nursery.start(my_server)\n        try:\n            yield value\n        finally:\n            # Kill the server when the scope exits\n            nursery.cancel_scope.cancel()\n```\n\nThis is the same, but back to 3.5:\n\n```python3\nfrom async_generator import async_generator, yield_, asynccontextmanager\n\n@asynccontextmanager\n@async_generator\nasync def background_server():\n    async with trio.open_nursery() as nursery:\n        value = await nursery.start(my_server)\n        try:\n            await yield_(value)\n        finally:\n            # Kill the server when the scope exits\n            nursery.cancel_scope.cancel()\n```\n\n(And if you're on 3.6, you can use `@asynccontextmanager` with\nnative generators.)\n\n# Let's do this\n\n- Install: `python3 -m pip install -U async_generator` (or on Windows,\n  maybe `py -3 -m pip install -U async_generator`\n- Manual: <https://async-generator.readthedocs.io/>\n- Bug tracker and source code: <https://github.com/python-trio/async_generator>\n- Real-time chat: <https://gitter.im/python-trio/general>\n- License: MIT or Apache 2, your choice\n- Contributor guide: <https://trio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/contributing.html>\n- Code of conduct: Contributors are requested to follow our [code of\n  conduct](https://trio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/code-of-conduct.html) in\n  all project spaces.\n\n# How come some of those links talk about \"trio\"?\n\n[Trio](https://trio.readthedocs.io) is a new async concurrency\nlibrary for Python that's obsessed with usability and correctness \u2013 we\nwant to make it *easy* to get things *right*. The `async_generator`\nlibrary is maintained by the Trio project as part of that mission, and\nbecause Trio uses `async_generator` internally.\n\nYou can use `async_generator` with any async library. It works great\nwith `asyncio`, or Twisted, or whatever you like. (But we think Trio\nis pretty sweet.)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "async_generator._tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "async_generator._version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "async_generator._version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "async_generator", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "async_generator.aclosing", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._util.aclosing", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.async_generator", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.async_generator", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.asynccontextmanager", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._util.asynccontextmanager", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.get_asyncgen_hooks", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.get_asyncgen_hooks", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.isasyncgen", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.isasyncgen", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.isasyncgenfunction", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.isasyncgenfunction", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.set_asyncgen_hooks", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.set_asyncgen_hooks", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.yield_", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.yield_", "project": null}}, {"name": "async_generator.yield_from_", "xref": {"fqname": "async_generator._impl.yield_from_", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.conftest", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "async_generator._tests.conftest.mock_sleep", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.conftest.pytest_pyfunc_call", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pyfuncitem", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Wrap any 'async def' tests so that they get automatically iterated.", "We used to use pytest-asyncio as a convenient way to do this, but nowadays", "pytest-asyncio uses us! In addition to it being generally bad for our test", "infrastructure to depend on the code-under-test, this totally messes up", "coverage info because depending on pytest's plugin load order, we might get", "imported before pytest-cov can be loaded and start gathering coverage."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "async_generator._util", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "async_generator._util.asynccontextmanager", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Like @contextmanager, but async."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "async_generator._util.aclosing", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "async_generator._util.aclosing.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "aiter", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._util.aclosing.__aenter__", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._util.aclosing.__aexit__", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name"