##########################################################"]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_isasyncgen", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["###############################################################", "introspection", "###############################################################"]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_isasyncgenfunction", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_isasyncgenfunction_is_not_inherited_by_wrappers", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Very subtle bug: functools.wraps copies across the entire contents of the", "wrapped function's __dict__. We used to use a simple _is_async_gen=True", "attribute to mark async generators. But if we do that, then simple wrappers", "like async_range_wrapper *do* return True for isasyncgenfunction. But that's", "not how inspect.isasyncgenfunction works, and it also caused problems for", "sphinxcontrib-trio, because given a function like:", "@acontextmanager", "@async_generator", "async def async_cm():", "...", "then we end up with async_cm introspecting as both an async context manager", "and an async generator, and it doesn't know who to believe. With the", "correct, inspect.isasyncgenfunction-compliant behavior, we have async_cm", "introspecting as an async context manager, and async_cm.__wrapped__", "introspecting as an async generator."]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_collections_abc_AsyncGenerator", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_ag_attributes", "asynchronous": true, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_refcnt", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.lets_exception_out", "asynchronous": true, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["###############################################################", "Edge cases", "###############################################################", "PEP 479: StopIteration or StopAsyncIteration exiting from inside an async", "generator should produce a RuntimeError with the __cause__ set to the", "original exception. Note that contextlib.asynccontextmanager depends on this", "behavior."]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_throw_StopIteration_or_StopAsyncIteration", "asynchronous": true, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_no_spurious_unawaited_coroutine_warning", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "recwarn", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["No \"coroutine was never awaited\" warnings for async generators that are not", "iterated"]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.local_asyncgen_hooks", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["###############################################################", "GC hooks", "###############################################################"]}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_gc_hooks_interface", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "local_asyncgen_hooks", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.test_gc_hooks_behavior", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "local_asyncgen_hooks", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.HasAsyncGenMethod", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.HasAsyncGenMethod.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "factor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.HasAsyncGenMethod.async_multiplied", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ait", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "async_generator._tests.test_async_generator.MyTestError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["###############################################################", "Exhausitve tests of the different ways to re-enter a coroutine.", "It used to be that re-entering via send/__next__ would work, but throw()", "immediately followed by an await yield_(...)  wouldn't work, and the", "YieldWrapper object would propagate back out to the coroutine runner.", "Before I fixed this, the 'assert value is None' check below would fail", "(because of the YieldWrapper leaking out), and if you removed that", "assertion, then the code would appear to run successfully but the final list", "would just be [1, 3] instead of [1, 2, 3].", "###############################################################"]}], "exports": []}]}